properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 11 at 11:37PM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...HEAVY LAKE EFFECT SNOW AFFECTING THE TWIN PORTS...

.Heavy lake effect snow bands have been streaming in off Lake
Superior and into the Twin Ports this evening. These snow bands
are expected to continue much of the night before the bands move
north of the area. Snowfall amounts will vary greatly in a short
distance, with locally higher amounts of 6 inches or more.

* WHAT...Heavy lake effect snow. Additional snow accumulations
of up to 3 inches, except up to one inch for northern Douglas
and Bayfield counties.

* WHERE...In Wisconsin, Douglas County. In Minnesota, Southern
Lake and Carlton and South St. Louis Counties. This includes
the Tribal Lands of the Fond du Lac Band.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST SUNDAY
